From: Calculinux Build Team <build@calculinux.org>
Subject: [PATCH] portduino: select buildroot board for Yocto builds

The buildroot board profile configures PlatformIO to reuse the cross
compiler and flags supplied via TARGET_* environment variables. Switching
Portduino's native environment to this board ensures the Yocto toolchain
is honoured instead of trying to detect and use the build host compiler.

Signed-off-by: Calculinux Build Team <build@calculinux.org>
Upstream-Status: Pending

---
 variants/portduino/platformio.ini | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/variants/portduino/platformio.ini
+++ b/variants/portduino/platformio.ini
@@ -1,7 +1,7 @@
 extends = portduino_base
 build_flags = ${portduino_base.build_flags} -I variants/portduino
   -D ARCH_PORTDUINO
-board = cross_platform
+board = buildroot
 lib_deps = ${portduino_base.lib_deps}
 build_src_filter = ${portduino_base.build_src_filter}
 
